article.headline: UC Davis edges Cal Poly in overtime 81-78

images.name: 1H UCD C. Hawkins made Three Point Jumper.
images.caption: 1H (19:23) UCD Corey Hawkins made Three Point Jumper.

article.linkText: UC Davis edges Cal Poly in overtime 81-78
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Josh Ritchart scored 24 points, including the 3-pointer that forced overtime, to help UC Davis to an 81-78 comeback win over Cal Poly on Saturday night. Trailing by 14 in the first half, UC Davis (16-4, 6-1 Big West) battled back during the second and tied the game at 65 with Ritchart's 3 to send the game into overtime. In OT, Cal Poly (10-10, 3-5) twice took the lead with layups from David Nwaba before Avery Johnson sank the go-ahead 3-pointer to give the Aggies the lead for good 72-71. Josh Fox and Corey Hawkins helped pad the advantage and Johnson sealed it with a pair of free throws with 3 seconds to go after Cal Poly again closed to within a point. Hawkins finished with 22 points and Johnson 11 as the Aggies shot 50.9 percent from the field. Brian Bennett led the Mustangs with 27 points.
